answerText: Pindar[10] The "Hymn to Aphrodite" is the only completely extant poem by this poet from Lesbos. Anne Carson's translation of her fragments is called If Not, Winter.

question: Question: Name some members of the nine lyric poets, for 10 points each. [10] This man's Pythian odes can be found in the four books he wrote of epinikia, the form for which he is best known.
